# Help: Block-layer features and tuning knobs
#
# Block-layer infrastructure not tied to any single driver:
# writeback throttling (BLK_WBT, BLK_WBT_MQ), block debugfs
# (BLK_DEBUG_FS), the SG v4 helper library (BLK_DEV_BSGLIB), runtime
# power management (BLK_PM), and self-encrypting drive management
# (BLK_SED_OPAL).
#
# Block device drivers live in storage/block-devices.config,
# storage/block-test-devices.config, and storage/nvme.config; this
# fragment is the layer underneath them.
#
# The multi-queue helpers (BLK_MQ_PCI, BLK_MQ_VIRTIO, BLK_MQ_STACKING)
# and the block-cgroup counters (BLK_CGROUP_PUNT_BIO, BLK_CGROUP_RWSTAT)
# are not set here: they are internal symbols with no prompt, selected
# automatically by the drivers and cgroup controllers that need them.
#
# Prerequisites inlined per the self-containment rule:
# - PM=y     gates BLK_PM (def_bool PM).
# - KEYS=y   gates BLK_SED_OPAL (SED key handling).
#
# Every symbol is bool. No builtin/ counterpart needed.
# See: block/Kconfig
# See: https://docs.kernel.org/block/index.html

#
# Inlined prerequisites
#
CONFIG_PM=y
CONFIG_KEYS=y

#
# Block-layer features
#
CONFIG_BLK_WBT=y
CONFIG_BLK_WBT_MQ=y
CONFIG_BLK_DEBUG_FS=y
CONFIG_BLK_DEV_BSGLIB=y
CONFIG_BLK_PM=y
CONFIG_BLK_SED_OPAL=y
